 for the 55+ wizzies out there, I notice that tears of druzzil has the dreaded force shock symbol on it.  Do tears of solusek and the other one have lower resists?  With a chanter in group tashing, I usually hit with all waves, but not so how without chanter =(  Would like to get this thread going since I really think these rains can go a long way to improving wiz efficiency since we don't get any better blasts till lure of ice and sunstrike.<br>
<br>
Syndrome<br>
53 wiz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthomus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thomus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/5/00 1:39:05 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tomkingis/tomjkingt.gif width=150 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tears line</span><hr size=1> I use Tears of Druzzil even without someone doing MR- Debuffing, however that is highly dependent on what and where I fight. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Even if only 2 ticks put in full damage it is still more efficient than Ice Comet.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Next level &quot;54&quot; we get Voltaic Draught a fast-casting mana-efficient magic based DD</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, a welcome DD over the dreaded and often resisted Draught of Fire.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> I have used ToD in Skyfire, Burningwoods and Trakanon's Teeth with acceptable results, getting in full damage drops mobs pretty damn fast, and with mana to spare.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The times ToD hits low or gets resisted is no different than using Ice Comet and getting a full out resist, and when you hit low with Ice Comet, it's usually something rediculous, know what I mean? <br>
<br>
Use ToD here and there to test it, it's much easier to test when you have someone to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> fear the mob with shackles slowing it down for all waves, or if you have someone chain stunning it</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, a lot of times when the mob is moving that 3rd tick will never happen.<br>
<br>
Wizards + Enchanters = Death Incarnate when coordinating AE's for maximum efficiency. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Every Wizard and Enchanter that ends up grouped together should discuss using AE's</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, you'll go through less mana, kill more mobs, what more could you ask for? =p<br>
<br>
~peace~ <p><img border="0" src="http://members.aol.com/tomkingis/thomus.jpg" width="161" height="235"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usyndromebrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SyndromeBrell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/5/00 3:26:18 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tears line</span><hr size=1> Agree 100%, havent tested out the fear+shackles, next time Im with a necro Ill have to.  The only problem I seem to have when using tears is that 1) someone will complain that it causes lag because they dont want to turn off particle effects, or 2) the enchanter is afraid(quite rare, only twice have enchanters refused to try chain stunning with it) that it will get us all killed ;P  glad to see I got a response, we don't have enogh people posting on finger wagglers =(<br>
<br>
Another thing I heard from a friend on Fennin, casting concussion as soon as you can after tears lets you avoid having it aggro on you, so it pretty much stays taunted on the tank(unless the first or second wave aggro it)<br>
<br>
Syndrome<br>
<br>
<br>
p.s. reread your post, Don't you love when IC hits for 12 damage ;( <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthomus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thomus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 1:46:13 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tomkingis/tomjkingt.gif width=150 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tears line</span><hr size=1> *nod*<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   I had a chance to try out Tears of Druzzil in Sebilis.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
The first was on a froggy Shaman near the zone-in point, full resists but our enchanter had not tash'd it yet.<br>
<br>
The next time, the first 2 waves on a froggy knight hit low damage, the third resisted and broke the mez on a froggy shaman next to me. I didn't use it until after it was below 40 percent health either. The Enchanter was doing MR-debuffing at that point <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;they don't like to because of the aggro factor apparently&quot;.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Anyhow, nothing bad happened as a result of using ToD, but the group pretty much said they don't like the aggro on AE's so not to use them, I'm sure this will vary group to group, but always check first.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>An interesting thing happened to me one-time in Burningwoods with ToD; I had cast ToD on a Wurm, and the 3rd tick hit a Giant next to it, this also happened in Skyfire as well a few times with a Wurm and Wyvern or Chromadac.</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>Note: A Bard's Fear is pretty effective as well, and you'll have less downtime.</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--></b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   I have some other interesting information about the use of certain Wizard Spells in Sebilis;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Dispelling with Annull Magic.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> The Froggy Wizards have a damage shield, it apparently is very weak, so don't bother dispelling them <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;this upsets the shamans because a spell they use that normally uses 250 mana ends up eating 500 mana if they are dispelled&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and Enchanters who <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;slow&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> mobs right away don't like having it dispelled.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Ice Comet and Draught of Fire.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Get resisted far too frequently, and low damages to the point of making them virtually useless in Sebilis, so what alternatives are there at 53? read on.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Lure of Frost.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Will land every time there, though not as mana efficient, overall through the course of the night, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>I think it ultimately makes up for low damage and resists with other spells,</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> with the only exception being the use of Rend, read on.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Rend.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Which is now <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;correctly&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> magic based, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;was ice based a while back&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, will consistantly land full damage, with only an occasional resist or low damage, also not as mana efficient, but not much else until we hit 54 and get Voltaic Draught. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Atol's Spectral Shackles.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Has a very high taunt factor on mobs in Sebilis, usually the fight will not last longer than the 2 minutes 30 seconds shackles will hold for, but if you cast it immediately and sit, you will have a froggy beating away at your manaskin. Wait until the mob is 75 percent health before casting it, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>and don't worry it won't break an Enchanters Mez</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->. Resists are sparse overall, and it's very effective, just make sure your out of range of getting yourself, but not far enough to attract other mobs in the radious.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Tishans Discord and Markers Clash.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Are <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;occasionally&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> useful. We had a rogue and they love stuns, I pointed out the taunt factor, and demonstrated what happens when you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;chain-cast&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> these two stuns, I didn't die thanks to our Cleric but the point was made. It appears to only be safe after the mob is below 50 percent health <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;meaning it's too pissed at the tanks&quot; and you want to toss in a complimentary stun.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>  Note: These also tend to get resisted alot above 50-75 percent health.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   All of the above spells &quot;other than AE's&quot; were tested on Beetles, Golems and Guardians as well.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Only other thing I can add to this is</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->; always keep mana ready for Evac <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;naturally&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, in fact I try to keep enough to be ready for a fizzle <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;very rare&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> but you never know. <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;Always&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> make sure you Snare, unless there is a Druid or Ranger in the group. Nuke at or below 40-50 percent, or you'll end up wasting precious Cleric mana, and get summoned while medding, again <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>   &quot;naturally&quot;</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->. Be prepared to be low on mana most, but not all of the time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>   Well, I do my best to try and guage things and make mental notes. I hope you find this information useful. You'll of course want to guage this yourself, but this might be useful information to someone, I hope.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
~peace~ <p><img border="0" src="http://members.aol.com/tomkingis/thomus.jpg" width="161" height="235"></p><i>Edited by <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthomus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thomus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 9/6/00 1:04:27 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/uthomus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Thomus</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 2:25:33 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/tomkingis/tomjkingt.gif width=150 height=150></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Tears line</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> About Concussion</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, I discussed this with Psychodelia and it is always mem'd, it is very useful for removing that instant attention Wizards can get from mobs, and it's not our shining personalities either. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> And YES I hate it when Ice Comet lands 12 damage</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, even funnier on those day's you nuke an orc pawn with it for the hell of it, or for bothering you at the spires while medding, and it runs away with minor damage on it! how embarassing!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Spell effects</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, bah! Tell them to suck it up and turn it off, if they let us use AE's more, there would be much more efficiency. Most Wizards I know give up on them after a couple shots at it, mostly because of groups frowning upon the use of AE's having had experiences with them, and believe in the old Myth that AE=Instant Death, which is only true if you don't have an Enchanter. <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> How are we ever going to perfect the use of them, and remove the bad experiences people claim to have had, if we don't get the chance to fine tune the use of AE's to begin with?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Tanks from what I can tell, like to focus on 1 mob at a time</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, I think that people find this less confusing to be honest. There are spells like Pilar of Frost, which are cool, but on frequent occasion will only hit 1 mob even when they are standing right next to each other, and it's designed to hit up to 4, so much for AE kiting eh? <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
~peace~ <p><img border="0" src="http://members.aol.com/tomkingis/thomus.jpg" width="161" height="235"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/ukurven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kurven</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 3:58:00 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Tears</span><hr size=1> I just hate how pets take up waves from the tear spells, i often group with pet classes making these spells alot less effective or even useless.<br>
<br>
Maybe they will someday fix this =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/bbrellserilis.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=maryinn>Maryinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 5:03:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   One note on mobs with O'Kiels and a comment</span><hr size=1> Wizards can dispel O'kiels by using their sol ro quest staff (the one that lowers cr and fr).  Because O'kiels has an fr component the use of the staff will dispell the fr component and also the ds component.  This is an easy way to remove the spam and ds without removing slows.  I assume it works the same way on Magician DS's because they have a FR buff component, but it won't work to remove the ranger and druid line of damage shields.<br>
<br>
If a wizard isn't using their AE spells at all their damage output over time is going to be very low (log it and see).  Get used to using them and convince your party to let you.  You can, at the very least, use the tears line on single mobs for some nice increases in efficieny.  In big raids where mobs don't last long and there is a lot of time between pulls wizards efficiency with just DD's is great, it's the single group situations where the efficiency problem pops up.<br>
<br>
-Maryinn of the Merry Band (Brell Serilis) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#313532><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/usyndromebrell.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SyndromeBrell</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 6:46:10 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: One note on mobs with O'Kiels and a comment</span><hr size=1> If you are just trying to eliminate the spam, verant added in an option to turn off damage shield messages.  Of course, if a ranger is tanking, smacking 10 times a round or so, I suppose that 2 points a shot can add up eventually...=) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#414141><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub3.ezboard.com/upsychodelia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Psychodelia</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Adventurer of Underfoot</span><br>   <font color=#CC9900>(9/6/00 10:44:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: One note on mobs with O'Kiels and a comment</span><hr size=1>    Im not that big a fan of AE, but I must say that it does come in handy under rare circumstances. I disagree that direct damage alone is not enough. Ive made some logs of the damage under different situations and its massive, especially for DD. I wanted to stress to everyone that its not the amount of damage you do over time that measures effectiveness, its the rate that the mob is killed as well. Although the tears line may do some more damage at those levels 50-55, its not a pure DD.<br>
<br>
    Wizards have the most powerful direct damage in the game for a reason. The reason that it is all they really have(no AC, hps, heals, melee) is because its the most powerful offense in Everquest. Rain spells, I think they are good, but not quite as reliable. Mobs move. IMO, the draught spells are excellent. Low taunt for such high damage too. And sunstrike, whohoaa!!! Ill let you see for yourself!  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 Essentialy, a wizard does their damage instantly and absolutely everytime they land these monsters. That saves the rest of the group from loosing hps/heal mana if it were to be meleed over time. One of the main reasons I play a wizard(besides teleportation) is because they make the slow draggy gameplay go so much faster and easier. It helps enchanters when you cut down those first couple of mobs fast. It helps clerics by allowing them to save their mana for when you run out.(hopefully when the tanks are finishing off that last poor mob) Direct damage is absolutely awesome. I didnt get to lev 60 from soloing or being &quot;inefficient&quot; to the group. I used draught for the entire trip. It depends on the enchanter really. With a good enchanter and clarity, a wizard will compliment the enchanters methods and keep the group in a controlled situation.<br>
<br>
<br>
   Oh yeah , one other thing. About snaring. I personally have found it more advantagous to use bonds of force rather than shackles. Shackled seems to have a bugged fizzle rate and costs more mana. Bonds of force works fine for me. I recomend using that as snarer, it seems more mana efficient.<br>
