I have to disagree with Psychodelia a little bit.<br>
Draught sucks.<br>
<br>
We have the same efficiency of DD from 51-56. This is really depressing because by using DD alone even a paladin can keep close to me in damage over time for a whole evening.<br>
At 57 we get a little bump, and all of a sudden at 60 we kick serious ass again. Its too long a wait imho.<br>
<br>
My hit rate on various appropriate draught spells runs at about 90%.<br>
Meaning it has a 2.8 : 1 damage to mana ratio.<br>
<br>
My hit rate with tears runs a little better than 67% giving it about a 3.2 : 1 damage to mana ratio. Solusek works better on some mobs, druzzil works better on other mobs.<br>
I need to come up with a more accurate number for this.<br>
<br>
I have looked at Psychodelia's logs with sunstrike and he was hitting for about 94% giving him about a 3.4 : 1 damage to mana ratio. (I believe the difference between 94% and 90% and is level 60 vs level 55)<br>
<br>
EVERY chance I get I use tears. When there is a single mob isolated from its friends. I am crying all over it.<br>
<br>
Going from a 2.8 to 3.2 dmg/mana ratio is a huge increase and i work real hard to do it.<br>
When teamed with a shaman AND an enchanter debuffing i am pretty sure i get tears up over 4 to 1 in efficiency. With that and lots of well controlled single mobs, I can actually deal the most damage in the party (of course not with a rogue or monk present, cough)<br>
<br>
The really sad thing is, when you are dungeon crawling and get hip-deep in mobs, you are stuck with DD. The enchanter is saving everyones ass, and you are using your 2nd best spells. Bleah.<br>
<br>
